then you'll get confused.

00:08:51.850 --> 00:08:55.580 align:middle line:84%
But if you know that it's like
a dream kind of type of thing,

00:08:55.580 --> 00:08:59.650 align:middle line:84%
more subtle, then you
can call it imagination.

00:08:59.650 --> 00:09:00.460 align:middle line:90%
But it's not.

00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:01.270 align:middle line:90%
It's very real.

00:09:01.270 --> 00:09:04.610 align:middle line:84%
It's actually that world that
we're speaking about now,

00:09:04.610 --> 00:09:05.420 align:middle line:90%
of the heart.

00:09:05.420 --> 00:09:08.480 align:middle line:90%
It's more real than this one.

00:09:08.480 --> 00:09:12.720 align:middle line:84%
Like everything that exists here
in 3D came from that source,

00:09:12.720 --> 00:09:14.150 align:middle line:90%
came from that world.

00:09:14.150 --> 00:09:16.950 align:middle line:84%
So we're like, for
example, we say,

00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:18.890 align:middle line:84%
oh, I've just been
dreaming this last night.

00:09:18.890 --> 00:09:21.485 align:middle line:90%
We don't give any reality.

00:09:21.485 --> 00:09:23.590 align:middle line:84%
We don't say it's true
because it's just a dream,

00:09:23.590 --> 00:09:26.032 align:middle line:84%
and all this is reality
because I can touch it.

00:09:26.032 --> 00:09:27.490 align:middle line:84%
But it's just the
other way around.

00:09:27.490 --> 00:09:29.040 align:middle line:84%
It's completely the
other way around.

00:09:29.040 --> 00:09:32.320 align:middle line:84%
Like everything we can touch
and everything we can see,

00:09:32.320 --> 00:09:37.750 align:middle line:84%
it's all coming from
this subtle, you know,

00:09:37.750 --> 00:09:39.350 align:middle line:90%
imagery type of world.

00:09:39.350 --> 00:09:42.730 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't see-- because
a lot of people see stuff--

00:09:42.730 --> 00:09:44.940 align:middle line:84%
I'm not such seer, so
I'm always jealous.

00:09:44.940 --> 00:09:49.030 align:middle line:84%
I'm like oh, they're seeing
auras and things and seers.

00:09:49.030 --> 00:09:50.770 align:middle line:90%
But you don't need to be a seer.

00:09:50.770 --> 00:09:53.720 align:middle line:84%
You can feel things,
or you can know things.

00:09:53.720 --> 00:09:55.490 align:middle line:90%
That's even more strong.

00:09:55.490 --> 00:09:57.490 align:middle line:90%
Like you just know it.

00:09:57.490 --> 00:09:58.794 align:middle line:90%
You're not seeing anything.

00:09:58.794 --> 00:09:59.960 align:middle line:90%
You're not sensing anything.

00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:02.570 align:middle line:84%
You're like feeling a
bit like oh, I'm blind.

00:10:02.570 --> 00:10:04.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm not-- but you know.

00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:04.910 align:middle line:90%
You know.

00:10:04.910 --> 00:10:08.280 align:middle line:84%
So there's many different
ways of communicating

00:10:08.280 --> 00:10:10.300 align:middle line:84%
with your heart,
let's say, or letting

00:10:10.300 --> 00:10:13.320 align:middle line:90%
your heart communicate to you.

00:10:13.320 --> 00:10:16.250 align:middle line:84%
And then, it just
starts flowing really.

00:10:16.250 --> 00:10:18.690 align:middle line:90%
It's very strong.

00:10:18.690 --> 00:10:21.723 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: Is there a process
to it, or how do you--

00:10:21.723 --> 00:10:25.720 align:middle line:84%
why do we say it's awakening
the illuminated heart?

00:10:25.720 --> 00:10:27.185 align:middle line:90%
Why illuminated?

00:10:27.185 --> 00:10:28.460 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: Yeah.

00:10:28.460 --> 00:10:31.530 align:middle line:84%
In the beginning, it was just
called Living in the Heart.

00:10:31.530 --> 00:10:33.590 align:middle line:84%
So we didn't call
it illuminated.

00:10:33.590 --> 00:10:36.570 align:middle line:84%
We didn't call it
even awakening.

00:10:36.570 --> 00:10:38.808 align:middle line:84%
We called it living
in the heart.

00:10:38.808 --> 00:10:41.590 align:middle line:90%
Then, actually, it was--

00:10:41.590 --> 00:10:44.520 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: You can hear the big
motor bikes and there's a big

00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:47.410 align:middle line:84%
road not far, so sorry for a
little bit of background noise.

00:10:47.410 --> 00:10:48.800 align:middle line:90%
But this is part of life, right?

00:10:48.800 --> 00:10:50.770 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we're in Montpellier.

00:10:50.770 --> 00:10:52.310 align:middle line:90%
Guys are a little bit crazy.

00:10:52.310 --> 00:10:55.252 align:middle line:90%
This is summertime.

00:10:55.252 --> 00:10:56.354 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: True.

00:10:56.354 --> 00:10:58.270 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: They're living
maybe in their heart.

00:10:58.270 --> 00:11:00.370 align:middle line:84%
We don't know which
place they live from.

00:11:00.370 --> 00:11:02.120 align:middle line:90%
But they're having some fun.

00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:02.740 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: True.

00:11:02.740 --> 00:11:05.970 align:middle line:90%


00:11:05.970 --> 00:11:08.460 align:middle line:84%
So in the beginning, we
called it Living in the Heart,

00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:10.890 align:middle line:84%
but then it was a
copyrighted, so we couldn't

00:11:10.890 --> 00:11:12.530 align:middle line:84%
call it Living in
the Heart anymore.

00:11:12.530 --> 00:11:15.310 align:middle line:84%
And then I was part of
the very first teacher

00:11:15.310 --> 00:11:17.240 align:middle line:90%
training with Drunvalo.

00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:18.470 align:middle line:90%
And so we said, OK.

00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:20.160 align:middle line:90%
So we have to have a new name.

00:11:20.160 --> 00:11:24.460 align:middle line:84%
So he asked 100 people and said
let's come up with a new name.

00:11:24.460 --> 00:11:25.930 align:middle line:90%
And then this was the result.

00:11:25.930 --> 00:11:27.480 align:middle line:90%
From these 100 people.

00:11:27.480 --> 00:11:29.250 align:middle line:84%
We all gave our
suggestions, and it

00:11:29.250 --> 00:11:31.850 align:middle line:84%
became Awakening the
Illuminated Heart.

00:11:31.850 --> 00:11:36.260 align:middle line:84%
But basically, what it really
is is it is an awakening.

00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:38.110 align:middle line:90%
It is a heart awakening.

00:11:38.110 --> 00:11:40.560 align:middle line:84%
But basically, what it is
it's living from the heart.

00:11:40.560 --> 00:11:43.340 align:middle line:84%
It's really-- you can
say there is a method--

00:11:43.340 --> 00:11:45.290 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: We have a
little cat behind us.

00:11:45.290 --> 00:11:46.160 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: Oh, nice.

00:11:46.160 --> 00:11:47.200 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: He's visiting.

00:11:47.200 --> 00:11:48.210 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: Yay!

00:11:48.210 --> 00:11:50.280 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: I don't know if
you're going to see it.

00:11:50.280 --> 00:11:51.605 align:middle line:90%
I think he wants to say hello.

00:11:51.605 --> 00:11:53.620 align:middle line:84%
He wants to live
in the heart, too.

00:11:53.620 --> 00:11:56.000 align:middle line:90%
They live the heart, don't they?

00:11:56.000 --> 00:11:57.570 align:middle line:90%
He's intrigued by your hat?

00:11:57.570 --> 00:11:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>> HIRA: That's exactly
where I want to go to.

00:11:59.560 --> 00:12:02.675 align:middle line:84%
It's like imagine that
you are painting something

00:12:02.675 --> 00:12:03.860 align:middle line:90%
or you're dancing.

00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:06.050 align:middle line:84%
You're listening to
music and you're dancing.

00:12:06.050 --> 00:12:08.070 align:middle line:84%
You are in your
heart at that moment.

00:12:08.070 --> 00:12:09.450 align:middle line:90%
You're completely in your heart.

00:12:09.450 --> 00:12:12.280 align:middle line:84%
When you are inspired,
when you are creative,

00:12:12.280 --> 00:12:15.780 align:middle line:84%
when you're channeling this love
that you have for the world,

00:12:15.780 --> 00:12:17.190 align:middle line:90%
you're in your heart.

00:12:17.190 --> 00:12:19.260 align:middle line:84%
The thing what we
learn in this workshop

00:12:19.260 --> 00:12:23.330 align:middle line:84%
is to also do it when somebody's
screaming at you, when

00:12:23.330 --> 00:12:26.580 align:middle line:84%
the neighbors are
criticizing you,

00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:29.210 align:middle line:84%
when people are
really hard on you.

00:12:29.210 --> 00:12:31.980 align:middle line:84%
That's when it's
important to really learn,

00:12:31.980 --> 00:12:34.500 align:middle line:84%
OK, I can deal with
this from my heart.

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:36.100 align:middle line:90%
I don't need to scream back.

00:12:36.100 --> 00:12:37.950 align:middle line:90%
I don't need to get upset.

00:12:37.950 --> 00:12:40.160 align:middle line:90%
I can deal with this.

00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:43.450 align:middle line:84%
So yes, we all have
spontaneous moments.

00:12:43.450 --> 00:12:45.850 align:middle line:84%
We are all the
time in our hearts.

00:12:45.850 --> 00:12:48.170 align:middle line:84%
But we just lose
ourselves, and that's

00:12:48.170 --> 00:12:53.287 align:middle line:84%
why it's nice to have kind of a
method to learn how to do this.

00:12:53.287 --> 00:12:55.370 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: I guess there's
different levels, right?

00:12:55.370 --> 00:12:58.060 align:middle line:84%
There's the day to day,
but there's all the way

00:12:58.060 --> 00:12:59.840 align:middle line:90%
to the ascension, et cetera.

00:12:59.840 --> 00:13:01.660 align:middle line:84%
So we can go a little
bit later on to that.

00:13:01.660 --> 00:13:03.730 align:middle line:84%
But the practical
aspect, day to day,

00:13:03.730 --> 00:13:07.057 align:middle line:84%
our heart has a tendency
to close and to shut down.

00:13:07.057 --> 00:13:08.765 align:middle line:84%
The main thing is to
keep the heart open.

00:13:08.765 --> 00:13:09.450 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: Exactly

00:13:09.450 --> 00:13:10.717 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: It's like boom.

00:13:10.717 --> 00:13:12.800 align:middle line:84%
Or we feel it, and then
there's something happens.

00:13:12.800 --> 00:13:15.510 align:middle line:84%
So how do we-- how
does that work?

00:13:15.510 --> 00:13:17.920 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: Yeah, it's a practice.

00:13:17.920 --> 00:13:18.840 align:middle line:90%
It's a practice.

00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:23.570 align:middle line:84%
I mean, some people think they
come and do a workshop with me

00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:26.310 align:middle line:84%
and they think, oh, she says
a living in the heart teacher

00:13:26.310 --> 00:13:29.640 align:middle line:84%
so she's probably like
a Buddha all the time.

00:13:29.640 --> 00:13:30.420 align:middle line:90%
I'm not.

00:13:30.420 --> 00:13:33.560 align:middle line:84%
I mean I have moments
where my ego takes over.

00:13:33.560 --> 00:13:36.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm not talking about the
ego in a negative sense.

00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:39.550 align:middle line:84%
A lot of teachers or
spiritual lineages

00:13:39.550 --> 00:13:42.070 align:middle line:84%
have been talking
negative about the ego.

00:13:42.070 --> 00:13:42.810 align:middle line:90%
I'm not.

00:13:42.810 --> 00:13:46.860 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying kind of respect
your ego, you know.

00:13:46.860 --> 00:13:48.380 align:middle line:90%
But just don't let it run you.

00:13:48.380 --> 00:13:51.020 align:middle line:90%
Don't let it control you.

00:13:51.020 --> 00:13:53.500 align:middle line:84%
But I also have moments
where my ego controls me,

00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:58.130 align:middle line:84%
where I'm a control freak or
I'm needy or I'm arrogant.

00:13:58.130 --> 00:13:59.710 align:middle line:90%
Whatever, you know.

00:13:59.710 --> 00:14:01.600 align:middle line:90%
So it's a practice.

00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:04.580 align:middle line:84%
It's like in the beginning,
I could recognize it,

00:14:04.580 --> 00:14:08.370 align:middle line:84%
but I would stay in that
ego for let's say hours.

00:14:08.370 --> 00:14:12.390 align:middle line:84%
And now I can recognize it
really fast, and I can say wow.

00:14:12.390 --> 00:14:13.680 align:middle line:90%
You know what?

00:14:13.680 --> 00:14:15.560 align:middle line:90%
That wasn't from my heart.

00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:16.610 align:middle line:90%
And I can take it back.

00:14:16.610 --> 00:14:20.510 align:middle line:84%
I go inside of my heart and
I totally, in the moment,

00:14:20.510 --> 00:14:23.300 align:middle line:84%
change the reality of the
a situation that I'm in.

00:14:23.300 --> 00:14:25.310 align:middle line:90%
I can do it faster now.

00:14:25.310 --> 00:14:26.590 align:middle line:90%
So it's kind of a practice.

00:14:26.590 --> 00:14:29.500 align:middle line:84%
Are you going to
recognize it, or are you

00:14:29.500 --> 00:14:31.870 align:middle line:84%
just going to go
on automatic pilot

00:14:31.870 --> 00:14:33.610 align:middle line:90%
on your ego for the whole day?

00:14:33.610 --> 00:14:36.273 align:middle line:84%
Or are you going
to say oh, wait.

00:14:36.273 --> 00:14:40.320 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: Most of us use
gratitude to reopen the heart

00:14:40.320 --> 00:14:42.470 align:middle line:10%
and try to just stop and
at least be conscious

00:14:42.470 --> 00:14:44.190 align:middle line:10%
of the situation in gratitude.

00:14:44.190 --> 00:14:45.720 align:middle line:84%
What are some of
the tools for you?

00:14:45.720 --> 00:14:46.900 align:middle line:90%
>> HIRA: You're right.

00:14:46.900 --> 00:14:48.710 align:middle line:90%
Gratitude, compassion.

00:14:48.710 --> 00:14:50.600 align:middle line:90%
Compassion is a really good one.

00:14:50.600 --> 00:14:54.600 align:middle line:84%
If somebody, I don't know,
starts screaming on you

00:14:54.600 --> 00:14:58.240 align:middle line:84%
instead of thinking, well,
what's this person doing?

00:14:58.240 --> 00:15:01.660 align:middle line:84%
You can feel that maybe
this person really

00:15:01.660 --> 00:15:04.210 align:middle line:84%
doesn't have the
tools that you have.

00:15:04.210 --> 00:15:08.760 align:middle line:84%
So that straight away
creates compassion.

00:15:08.760 --> 00:15:09.550 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, like--

00:15:09.550 --> 00:15:10.800 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Stopping everything.

00:15:10.800 --> 00:15:12.440 align:middle line:84%
>> HIRA: Yeah,
stopping everything.

00:15:12.440 --> 00:15:13.550 align:middle line:90%
I love that one.

00:15:13.550 --> 00:15:15.650 align:middle line:90%
Just stop everything.

00:15:15.650 --> 00:15:19.790 align:middle line:84%
Like that's what you learn when
you do a lot of meditation.

00:15:19.790 --> 00:15:22.570 align:middle line:84%
That's also kind one of
the keys of this workshop,

00:15:22.570 --> 00:15:26.570 align:middle line:84%
is that you learn to live
in unity consciousness.

00:15:26.570 --> 00:15:28.900 align:middle line:84%
So instead of looking
at a situation saying

00:15:28.900 --> 00:15:33.220 align:middle line:84%
this is bad, this is good,
staying in this duality;

00:15:33.220 --> 00:15:35.510 align:middle line:84%
you pull yourself
out of it, and you

00:15:35.510 --> 00:15:39.260 align:middle line:84%
say what's the
unity consciousness

00:15:39.260 --> 00:15:40.630 align:middle line:90%
way of looking at this?

00:15:40.630 --> 00:15:43.140 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as you plug
into that, whatever

00:15:43.140 --> 00:15:45.470 align:middle line:84%
is your way as you
say-- compassion,

00:15:45.470 --> 00:15:49.910 align:middle line:84%
gratitude-- just stop
everything basically.

00:15:49.910 --> 00:15:55.050 align:middle line:84%
And don't pull or
don't you push.

00:15:55.050 --> 00:15:57.970 align:middle line:84%
Just look at it,
observe it simply

00:15:57.970 --> 00:16:01.120 align:middle line:84%
as it is, then if you do that
like a few seconds already

00:16:01.120 --> 00:16:02.690 align:middle line:90%
you are in unity consciousness.

00:16:02.690 --> 00:16:03.530 align:middle line:90%
You're there.

00:16:03.530 --> 00:16:05.970 align:middle line:84%
If you can prolong
that, if you can

00:16:05.970 --> 00:16:10.060 align:middle line:84%
keep that going more than
an hour, you're in bliss.

00:16:10.060 --> 00:16:11.380 align:middle line:90%
You're in complete bliss.

00:16:11.380 --> 00:16:13.380 align:middle line:84%
If you can do that for
two hours, three hours,

00:16:13.380 --> 00:16:14.629 align:middle line:90%
you can do that the whole day.

00:16:14.629 --> 00:16:16.850 align:middle line:90%
You are there.

00:16:16.850 --> 00:16:20.236 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: What is your
spin on enlightenment?

00:16:20.236 --> 00:16:22.820 align:middle line:10%
>> HIRA: My spin on
enlightenment is a very

00:16:22.820 --> 00:16:24.080 align:middle line:10%
interesting question.

00:16:24.080 --> 00:16:26.410 align:middle line:10%
Because it's not so easy.

00:16:26.410 --> 00:16:30.480 align:middle line:84%
But I would say that
ascension and enlightenment,

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:33.190 align:middle line:84%
they kind of like
come together for me.

00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:37.160 align:middle line:84%
Like there's different
ways, many different ways,

00:16:37.160 --> 00:16:40.870 align:middle line:84%
to get enlightened or
awake or to ascend.

00:16:40.870 --> 00:16:42.550 align:middle line:90%
Many different ways.

00:16:42.550 --> 00:16:46.810 align:middle line:84%
And so at a certain point,
they become one for me.

00:16:46.810 --> 00:16:52.300 align:middle line:84%
If you really start ascending,
what is ascension is basically

00:16:52.300 --> 00:16:55.555 align:middle line:84%
it's that your vibration
of your signature--

00:16:55.555 --> 00:16:59.530 align:middle line:84%
let's say your vibrational
signature of who you are--

00:16:59.530 --> 00:17:01.550 align:middle line:84%
is getting higher and
higher and higher.

00:17:01.550 --> 00:17:05.640 align:middle line:84%
Your energy level gets
vibrating higher and higher.

00:17:05.640 --> 00:17:07.790 align:middle line:84%
So the more that you
ascend, the more kind

00:17:07.790 --> 00:17:10.550 align:middle line:84%
of light or love
or higher vibration

00:17:10.550 --> 00:17:11.899 align:middle line:90%
that you're pulling in.

00:17:11.899 --> 00:17:13.940 align:middle line:84%
So the more that you do
that, of course, the more

00:17:13.940 --> 00:17:15.079 align:middle line:90%
that you are awake.

00:17:15.079 --> 00:17:18.790 align:middle line:10%
So for me, it's all--
at a certain point,

00:17:18.790 --> 00:17:20.259 align:middle line:10%
it all becomes one.

00:17:20.259 --> 00:17:21.886 align:middle line:10%
It's all the same.

00:17:21.886 --> 00:17:26.619 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: All the rest is
terms and vocabulary and words.

00:17:26.619 --> 00:17:27.470 align:middle line:10%
>> HIRA: True.

00:17:27.470 --> 00:17:30.730 align:middle line:10%
And different ways that
are all respectable.

00:17:30.730 --> 00:17:34.380 align:middle line:10%
Some people work harder
with different methods.

00:17:34.380 --> 00:17:38.300 align:middle line:84%
But some people just like
there's this beautiful story

00:17:38.300 --> 00:17:39.930 align:middle line:90%
that I love of the Buddha.

00:17:39.930 --> 00:17:43.900 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point, he takes
a flower and he turns it,

00:17:43.900 --> 00:17:46.820 align:middle line:84%
and the person that
looks at it and smiles

00:17:46.820 --> 00:17:50.070 align:middle line:84%
will be the one who
is his successor.

00:17:50.070 --> 00:17:52.720 align:middle line:10%
It's a very simple
story, but it shows

00:17:52.720 --> 00:17:58.010 align:middle line:10%
that it can be very simple
but at the same time

00:17:58.010 --> 00:18:01.060 align:middle line:10%
we have all different
ways of getting there.

00:18:01.060 --> 00:18:02.870 align:middle line:10%
There's no one way.

00:18:02.870 --> 00:18:05.365 align:middle line:84%
There's millions of
ways to get there.

00:18:05.365 --> 00:18:09.560 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: So the main thing,
whatever way we take is to take

